results.name: Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} 1/phi(k)^3, where phi is the Euler totient function.
comment: Sum_{k>=1} 1/phi(k)^m is convergent iff m > 1 (reference Monier). - _Bernard Schott_, Jan 14 2021
reference: Jean-Marie Monier, Analyse, Exercices corrigés, 2ème année MP, Dunod, 1997, Exercice 3.2.21, pp. 281 and 294.
link: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Totient Function.
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Totient Summatory Function.
mathematica: $MaxExtraPrecision = 1000; f[p_] := (1 + 1/((1 - 1/p)^s * (p^s - 1))) /. s -> 3; Do[cc = Rest[CoefficientList[Series[Log[f[1/x]], {x, 0, m}], x]]; Print[f[2] * Exp[N[Sum[Indexed[cc, n]*(PrimeZetaP[n] - 1/2^n), {n, 2, m}], 120]]], {m, 100, 1000, 100}]
